<section>
  <h2>Install &amp; Setup</h2>

  <h3>1. Install</h3>
  <pre><code class="language-sh">curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/brennanbrown/writer-cli/main/INSTALL.sh | bash</code></pre>
  <p>
    After the installer finishes, reload your shell profile so <code>writer</code> is available in the current terminal:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-sh">source ~/.bashrc   # bash
source ~/.zshrc    # zsh</code></pre>
  <p>Or via Homebrew (macOS / Linux):</p>
  <pre><code class="language-sh">brew tap brennanbrown/writer
brew install writer</code></pre>
  <p>Or via Basher:</p>
  <pre><code class="language-sh">basher install brennanbrown/writer-cli</code></pre>
  <p>Or clone and symlink manually:</p>
  <pre><code class="language-sh">git clone https://github.com/brennanbrown/writer-cli
ln -s "$PWD/writer-cli/writer.sh" ~/.local/bin/writer</code></pre>

  <h3>2. Run setup</h3>
  <pre><code class="language-sh">writer --setup</code></pre>
  <p>
    The wizard asks ten questions: your SSG, build command, content directory, editor, timezone, etc.
    Each prompt shows the current default. Press Enter to keep it.
    You only need to do this once.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you skip setup and run <code>writer</code> directly, the wizard starts automatically on first run.
  </p>

  <h3>3. Write</h3>
  <pre><code class="language-sh">writer on-the-meaning-of-home</code></pre>
  <p>
    The <strong>slug</strong>, the part after <code>writer</code>, becomes the URL path for your post.
    Keep it lowercase, use hyphens for spaces, letters and numbers only.
  </p>

